    "body": "### Problem\n\nExecuting `:redrawstatus` inside `on_detach` can lead to `E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: 1` error in some cases. This, for example, affects doing 'redrawstatus' inside `DiagnosticChanged` callback, as it can be triggered inside [`on_detach` from LSP](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/878b3b89c316138d99f9dbc47c84f2f94591df03/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua#L911).\n\n#28084 is possibly related (cc @seandewar), but it shows error while unloading is performed inside `on_detach`. The currently described issue results in an error with `on_detach` only accessing data and not doing any action.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following 'init.lua':\n    ```lua\n    -- Make `on_detach` redraw statusline\n    _G.attach_redrawstatus = function()\n      local buf_id = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\n      vim.api.nvim_buf_attach(buf_id, false, {\n        on_detach = function()\n          -- Using `vim.api.nvim__redraw({ buf = buf_id, statusline = true })`\n          -- does not show the error in this particular repro, but in real world\n          -- use case still shows several `E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: 1` errors.\n          --\n          -- Using `vim.schedule(vim.cmd.redrawstatus)` fixes the issue completely.\n          vim.cmd.redrawstatus()\n        end,\n      })\n    end\n\n    -- Set up tabline that accesses buffer-local option of scratch buffer\n    local scratch_buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n\n    _G.make_tabline_string = function()\n      -- NOTE: actual option name doesn't seem to matter, i.e. can be 'buftype' or\n      -- something else\n      local _ = vim.bo[scratch_buf_id].buflisted\n      return 'Hello'\n    end\n\n    vim.o.tabline = '%!v:lua.make_tabline_string()'\n    vim.o.showtabline = 2\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n3. `:lua attach_redrawstatus()`\n4. `:bwipeout`. Should show the `E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: 1` error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExecuting `:redrawstatus` inside `on_detach` does not lead to errors.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1698+gaa976f0d93\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.12.10-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.0-arch\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
